# Cursor Rules for trilpai.github.io

## Project Context
Static website for Trilp AI - a software consulting studio. Features the "3 Octaves" engineering philosophy and interactive browser games.

## Tech Stack
- Static HTML (no framework)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (compiled via CLI)
- Vanilla JavaScript ES6+ (IIFE pattern)
- GitHub Pages deployment

## Critical Rules

### CSS
- ONLY edit `assets/css/tailwind.css` - this is the source file
- NEVER edit `assets/css/style.css` - it is compiled output
- Use existing `@theme` tokens for colors (brand-blue, brand-lightblue, etc.)
- Maintain CSS custom properties in `:root` for layout values

### JavaScript
- Use IIFE pattern with 'use strict'
- No external dependencies or frameworks
- Use IntersectionObserver for visibility detection
- Throttle scroll handlers with requestAnimationFrame
- Game state uses localStorage with `trilpai_` prefix

### HTML
- Semantic HTML5 with ARIA attributes
- Include skip-to-content links for accessibility
- Maintain JSON-LD structured data blocks
- Use data-nav attributes for navigation highlighting

## Code Style
- 2 spaces indentation
- Single quotes in JavaScript
- Trailing commas (ES5 style)
- LF line endings
- Format with Prettier

## File Patterns
- `*.html` - Static pages with inline structured data
- `assets/css/tailwind.css` - Tailwind source (edit this)
- `assets/css/style.css` - Compiled CSS (do not edit)
- `assets/js/*.js` - Vanilla JavaScript modules
- `docs/*.md` - Documentation and philosophy content

## Brand Colors
```
brand-blue: #002b5b
brand-lightblue: #4f9df7
brand-red: #d72638
ink: #0b1220
paper: #ffffff
accent: #facc15
```

## Commands
```bash
npm run build   # Compile Tailwind CSS
npm run watch   # Watch mode for development
```

## Avoid
- Adding npm dependencies
- Using build frameworks (Webpack, Vite, etc.)
- Editing compiled CSS files
- Inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- Breaking accessibility features
